{
  "texts": [
    "These approaches excel at preserving the spatial continuity of fossil structures, which is essential for reconstructing fragmented specimens.",
    "However, scalability remains a challenge; the computational demands of 3D segmentation models are significantly higher than those of their 2D counterparts, limiting their practical application to smaller datasets or specific fossil types.",
    "Additionally, while these models perform well in controlled settings, their generalization across varying fossil preservation conditions and sedimentary matrices requires further investigation.",
    "Another trend in the field is the adoption of advanced loss functions specifically designed for segmentation tasks, such as dice loss, topology-aware loss, and focal loss.",
    "These loss functions help address the challenges associated with imbalanced class distributions and the preservation of intricate topological structures."
  ]
}